## Session goals

In this workshop, members practiced loading tabular data, validating column types, and building grouped summaries suitable for reporting.

## Key takeaways

- Use `info()` early to check null counts and data types.
- Build reusable cleaning functions instead of hard-coding one-off transforms.
- Validate grouped results with row counts to avoid aggregation mistakes.

## Follow-up

Use the Colab notebook to complete the optional challenge section on custom feature engineering.
